This paper deals with formalisms in logics of agency, which are typically studied in the subfield of computational logic (cs.CL) and formal methods (cs.FM). However, the paper focuses on sequent calculi and relational semantics, which are more closely related to proof theory (cs.LO) and mathematical logic (cs.LO, cs.MS). Additionally, the paper discusses the specific formalisms of STIT logics with temporal operators, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper's focus on cut-free calculi and structural properties suggests a connection to software engineering (cs.SE).
